---
name: scljet-sql-index-descent
description: SclJet O(log n) index descent — WHERE indexedcol=K prunes to the matching subtrees of a multi-level index; matches reference sqlite3
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet index descent (multi-level index)

Beyond the ordered index walk, a `WHERE <indexed col> = K` now descends the index B-tree in O(log n):
at each interior node it reads the divider key records and recurses only into the children whose
divider range could contain K (conservative `<=`/`>=` on the first key column, so equal-key runs that
straddle a divider are never missed); leaves yield the matching rowids, which are point-looked-up.
Falls back to the ordered walk on any bail (overflow divider/leaf, unexpected page). This fixture
uses long (40-char) text keys so 40 rows span several index leaves under an interior node — the
descent's interior path is exercised (verified separately that it does not fall back). Every result
matches reference sqlite3 (verified out-of-band); locked across `[int, js]`.

[ByteSlice, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlText, buildTableWithIndexDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)
[queryImage, renderRows](std/scljet/sql.ssc)

```scalascript
def show(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): Unit =
  queryImage(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) => println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
    case Right(rows) => println(sql + " => " + renderRows(rows).toString)

var pfx = ""
var p = 0
while p < 40 do
  pfx = pfx + "k"
  p = p + 1

var rowsRev: List[List[SqliteValue]] = Nil
var i = 1
while i <= 40 do
  rowsRev = List(SqlText(pfx + (i % 8).toString), SqlInteger(i.toLong)) :: rowsRev
  i = i + 1

buildTableWithIndexDatabase(512, 1, 1, "t", "CREATE TABLE t(k TEXT, v INTEGER)", "idx_k",
  "CREATE INDEX idx_k ON t(k)", List(0), rowsRev.reverse) match
  case Left(error) => println("build-error:" + error.message)
  case Right(db) =>
    show(db, "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM t WHERE k = '" + pfx + "3'")
    show(db, "SELECT v FROM t WHERE k = '" + pfx + "3' ORDER BY v")
    show(db, "SELECT v FROM t WHERE k = '" + pfx + "0' ORDER BY v")
    show(db, "SELECT MAX(v) FROM t WHERE k = '" + pfx + "7'")
    show(db, "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM t WHERE k = '" + pfx + "9'")
```
